Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Renal function is impaired, as indicated by elevated creatinine. Lipid profile shows mildly elevated total and LDL cholesterol, which may increase cardiovascular risk. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal insufficiency and consideration of lipid management.
